  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Within the academic community, there is genuine concern that use of AI will result in cases of plagiarism, particularly if academic writers do not think critically about the suggestions made by an AI and merely adopt and use whatever it recommends (Salvagno et al., 2023).",
    "Additionally, GenAI can reflect any bias contained in training data or held by its developers.",
    "As a result, by over-relying on GenAI without applying an appropriate level of skepticism, academic writers could help perpetuate such bias (Salvagno et al., 2023).",
    "While educators and researchers are expressing these ethical concerns, the degree to which students themselves are wrestling with these issues remains underexplored and the voices of students who use GenAI are lacking.",
    "Therefore, insights from students, who come from diverse backgrounds and are the primary users of such tools, are crucial for a comprehensive understanding of their effectiveness."
  ],
